==========================================================
Maven Project: Demo Heart App for EC2
==========================================================

Step 1: Verify Java and Maven
--------------------------------
Commands:
    java -version
    mvn -v
Purpose:
    Ensure Java and Maven are installed and working.

Step 2: Create Maven Project
--------------------------------
Command:
    mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=demo-app-for-ec2-instance \
    -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false
Purpose:
    Creates a basic Maven Java project with standard folder structure.

Step 3: Navigate to project folder
--------------------------------
Command:
    cd demo-app-for-ec2-instance

Step 4: Set Java version in pom.xml
--------------------------------
Edit pom.xml to include:
<properties>
    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>
    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>
</properties>
Purpose:
    Ensure project compiles using Java 17.

Step 5: Update App.java
--------------------------------
Replace default main method with:

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        String[] heart = {
            "  ***     ***  ",
            " *****   ***** ",
            "******* *******",
            "***************",
            " ************* ",
            "  ***********  ",
            "   *********   ",
            "    *******    ",
            "     *****     ",
            "      ***      ",
            "       *       "
        };

        for (String line : heart) {
            System.out.println(line);
            Thread.sleep(100);
        }

        System.out.println();
        System.out.println("üíñ Jai ‚ù§Ô∏è Dhana üíñ");
        System.out.println("‚ú® Forever Together ‚ú®");
        System.out.println();
        System.out.println("  Sending love from your EC2 instance! üòé");
    }
}

Purpose:
    Prints a cute ASCII heart with names and emojis in the console.

Step 6: Build the project
--------------------------------
Command:
    mvn clean install
Outcome:
    - Compiles code
    - Runs tests
    - Creates target/demo-app-for-ec2-instance-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

Step 7: Run the project
--------------------------------
Command:
    java -cp target/demo-app-for-ec2-instance-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.example.App
Outcome:
    Displays ASCII heart and emoji message in console.

Step 8: Push to GitHub via SSH
--------------------------------
1. Check Git status:
    git status
2. Add changes:
    git add .
3. Commit:
    git commit -m "Add ASCII heart and emoji output for Dhana"
4. Push:
    git push origin main
Purpose:
    Updates the repository with your latest changes.

==========================================================
Notes:
- Use SSH for secure GitHub pushes without password prompts.
- ASCII and emoji output is for fun and personalization.
- Maven target folder contains compiled JAR files.
==========================================================

